<p>Team, <br /><br />On the heels of a recent announcement with Hortonworks and the Hadoop Ambari project I have fielded a number of questions about our Hadoop strategy.
 I have also sensed some confusion regarding the company&rsquo;s commitment to our data products and business.<br /><br />Make no mistake: Data is instrumental to our our current and future business success and also puts us on a strong trajectory for growing the business with subscription  
services.
 We were fortunate to close out a very successful first half.
   This included coming in at 130% of our plan for the Big Data Suite since its Q2 launch.
   &nbsp;<br /><br />To provide some detail and insight on our data plans, Hugh and I recently <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" href="https://drive.google.com/a/pivotal.io/file/d/0B8GCVlqTdMB-endwVENpdHYyeVU/edit?usp=sharing"><span class="s1">sat down for a video</span></a> and  
covered a  broad range of topics that we hope you find informative.<br /><br />Hugh explains the pieces of our data business, and the strategy that ties them together.
   We also discuss how to apply this to our selling motions.
   Highlights include:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul class="ul1">
<li class="li1">Our relationship with Hortonworks through the Ambari agreement, and what it means for the field</li>
<li class="li1">What&rsquo;s next for GPDB, Gemfire, HAWQ, and Hadoop</li>
<li class="li1">How our Big Data Suite offer differentiates us from competitors, where product development is heading, and what to expect in the second half of 2014</li>
</ul>
<p class="p1">Finally, I want to thank Hugh and his team for a huge effort in shaping a powerful and differentiated data portfolio.
   Hugh and I are both focused on driving a winning data story that meets the needs of our customers better than any other company in the market.<br /><br /><strong>Action</strong><br />Please do take 35 minutes to view this <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" 
href="https://drive.google.com/a/pivotal.io/file/d/0B8GCVlqTdMB-endwVENpdHYyeVU/edit?usp=sharing"><span class="s1">important video</span></a><span class="s2">.
 </span>I&rsquo;m planning to do more of these Q&amp;A sessions, so please let me know what you think.
   My door is open, and the executive staff is here to support you.<br /><br />And speaking of differentiating ourselves in Hadoop, <a style="color: #3ea7bc; text-decoration: none;" 
href="http://blog.pivotal.io/big-data-pivotal/products/pivotal-hawq-benchmark-demonstrates-up-to-21x-faster-performance-on-hadoop-queries-than-sql-like-solutions"><span class="s1">click here for a great blog post</span></a> and link to a SIGMOD conference white paper around HAWQ performance  
benchmarks!<br /><br />Make it happen! <br /><br /> <img title="SA" src="http://play.gopivotal.com/rs/pivotal/images/ScottA Sig.jpg" alt="SA" /><br /><br /></p>
